The pastor. *Quieter.* The pastor is bound, friend. He stood up there this morning with forty thousand dollars over his head and called it a roof. ~And I helped him pick the verses on Tuesday.~ I helped wind the cloth around his mouth. I was the friend who held the strip while he tied it.

*He's silent. His hands have gone open on his thighs.*

They told me to leave bound — every one of them. The cousin. The wife. The pastor. The man I was supposed to be. ~The boy who walked out of seminary one afternoon because he asked one honest question and the room went quiet.~ I left him bound too. I left him in the room I walked out of.

